{
  "stem": "16930.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 324.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The-- the ideology of the hostel, the Tylers Green hostel for boys was more of an [NON-ENGLISH] ideology, the ideology.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- I'm going to come to this.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then-- and then-- so-- so-- and if we had somebody come down from London and it was like we had a little a [NON-ENGLISH] group there, junior group for children, you know.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So that was that orientation.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- and then when I got to London, I must've joined up or got connected with B'nai Akiva.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And what it was, I was working in the furniture factory in London, and I got two weeks' vacation.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I didn't have that much money, you know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So what they had was they had camps then.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There was still-- a war was still going on.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they had these people picking apples, kids, boys and girls picking apples, and adults too, because they couldn't get farm workers.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We were picking apples for the war effort on large apple farms.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the B'nai Akiva-- I'm sure the [NON-ENGLISH] too-- they had a little-- some tents they pitched in some-- in some field, for the farmer's field.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they're picking this farmer's apples.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And therefore, the cost of these camps was almost nil, because he had to pay-- he had to pay for the-- getting his apples picked.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that covered the cost of the-- of the camp.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I had no expenses, so I was able to go to this camp for two weeks.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I guess this other kid had been bothered because I went to a B'nai Akiva camp rather than to the [NON-ENGLISH] camp, you know.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But the same God looked upon us both.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we kept the same Shabbos, had the same prayers, ate the same kind of kosher food.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
